#
# Recipe Bottle Regime Vessel - Graft Demo
#
# Teaching target for graft mode. No Dockerfile, no nameplate, no crucible
# integration — this vessel never runs in a Crucible. The learner builds an
# image locally, anoints this vessel with it, grafts it via ordain, and
# inspects the GRAFTED vouch verdict; Assay: Supply Chain (onboarding track
# 13) uses this vessel to contrast graft against conjure and bind.

# Core Identity
RBRV_SIGIL=rbev-graft-demo
RBRV_DESCRIPTION="Teaching vessel for graft mode — local image pushed to GAR, no Dockerfile"

# Vessel Mode
RBRV_VESSEL_MODE=rbnve_graft

# Egress Mode
RBRV_EGRESS_MODE=rbnve_tether

# Tool Image Reliquary
RBRV_RELIQUARY=

# Grafting Configuration — rewritten by the anoint verb (rbw-rva) from the
# previous build's chained facts: run a build (kludge or ordain), anoint this
# vessel as the very next command, then commit the change. The value below is
# the last anointed image; the placeholder marks a never-anointed slot.
RBRV_GRAFT_IMAGE=

# eof
